# throughline · docker-compose environment template.
#
#   cp .env.example.compose .env
#   # Edit .env (at minimum set one LLM provider API key), then:
#   docker compose up -d
#
# Only ONE provider key is actually required — pick whichever
# matches the wizard's step 4 choice. Leave the rest empty (or
# delete the lines); the daemon auto-detects whichever var has a
# value.
#
# See docs/DEPLOYMENT.md §Pluggable backends for the full
# provider list + signup URLs.

# ======================================================================
# REQUIRED — pick ONE provider and fill in its API key.
# Comment/delete the rest.
# ======================================================================

# Multi-vendor proxy (300+ models via one key):
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=

# Direct providers:
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=
# XAI_API_KEY=

# Hosted open-weights:
# TOGETHER_API_KEY=
# FIREWORKS_API_KEY=
# GROQ_API_KEY=

# China-market:
# SILICONFLOW_API_KEY=
# MOONSHOT_API_KEY=
# DASHSCOPE_API_KEY=
# ZHIPU_API_KEY=
# ARK_API_KEY=      # Doubao

# Local / self-hosted (point at host from Docker):
# OLLAMA_API_KEY=   # optional; Ollama doesn't require a key
# Remember: to reach host Ollama from the daemon container, set
#   THROUGHLINE_LLM_URL=http://host.docker.internal:11434/v1
# and use the `generic` wizard provider.

# ======================================================================
# Backend picks. Safe defaults work for most users.
# ======================================================================

# Override which provider the daemon routes through. Normally
# auto-detected from whichever API key env var is set above; only
# set this if you have multiple keys and want to force one.
# THROUGHLINE_LLM_PROVIDER=openrouter

# Embedder:
#   openai  (default for compose — calls your LLM provider's embeddings
#            endpoint; cheap and runs in the small image)
#   bge-m3  (requires building with INSTALL_LOCAL=1; downloads a
#            ~4.6 GB model on first use; fully local)
EMBEDDER=openai

# Reranker:
#   skip    (default for compose; no cross-encoder pass)
#   cohere  (hosted; set COHERE_API_KEY)
#   bge-reranker-v2-m3 (local; requires INSTALL_LOCAL=1)
RERANKER=skip

# If RERANKER=cohere:
# COHERE_API_KEY=

# ======================================================================
# Build mode.
# ======================================================================
# INSTALL_LOCAL=0 — default. Small image (~400 MB); the torch /
#                   transformers deps are NOT installed. You must
#                   use a cloud embedder (EMBEDDER=openai / …) and
#                   RERANKER=skip | cohere.
# INSTALL_LOCAL=1 — full image (~3 GB). Local bge-m3 + bge-reranker
#                   modes available; set EMBEDDER=bge-m3.
INSTALL_LOCAL=0

# ======================================================================
# Refine daemon knobs (optional).
# ======================================================================

# Daily budget cap — daemon pauses refines when today's spend hits this.
# daily_budget_usd=20.0 is the wizard default; override here if you
# want a tighter cap in the containerised setup.
# THROUGHLINE_MAX_DAILY_USD=5.0

# Slow down the refine pipeline for fragile networks.
# REFINE_DEBOUNCE_SECONDS=5
# REFINE_MAX_RETRY=2
